s%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putin%20Calls%20For%20Zelensky's%20Removal%20As%20Ukraine%20Negotiations%20Face%20Uncertainty%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20upped%20the%20ante%20in%20the%20negotiations%20to%20end%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20Going%20straight%20for%20the%20head%2C%20he%20has%20called%20for%20Zelensky's%20removal%20as%20Ukraine's%20President%20and%20instead%2C%20put%20in%20place%20a%20%26quot%3Btransitional%20administration%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Putin%20has%20also%20ordered%20his%20armed%20forces%20to%20%26quot%3Bfinish%20off%26quot%3B%20any%20and%20all%20Ukrainian%20troops%20as%20Moscow%20finds%20itself%20in%20a%20position%20of%20dominance%2C%20both%20on%20the%20battlefield%20as%20well%20as%20the%20negotiating%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20rapprochement%20between%20Washington%20and%20Moscow%20since%20Donald%20Trump's%20return%20to%20office%20and%20the%20US%20leader's%20threats%20to%20stop%20supporting%20Kyiv%20have%20bolstered%20President%20Putin's%20confidence%20more%20than%20three%20years%20into%20the%20war%20in%20which%20tens%20of%20thousands%20have%20died%20on%20both%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%2C%20from%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%2C%20maintained%20that%20it%20is%20because%20of%20Ukraine%20decision%20to%20join%20NATO%20and%20arming%20itself%20against%20Russia%2C%20that%20sparked%20the%20war.%20Moscow%20blames%20President%20Zelensky%20for%20such%20miscalculated%20geopolitical%20manoeuvres%20creating%20a%20ever-expanding%20rift%20between%20Russia%20and%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPUTIN'S%20TOUGH%20TALK%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20President%20Putin%20and%20President%20Zelensky%20detest%20each%20other.%20Both%20avoid%20direct%20communication%2C%20and%20instead%2C%20speak%20to%20interlocutors%20at%20neutral%20venues.%20The%20US%2C%20under%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20leadership%20is%20facilitating%20these%20talks.%20Ukraine%20fears%20it%20could%20be%20forced%20to%20accept%20a%20final%20peace%20deal%20on%20terms%20that%20are%20favourable%20to%20Moscow.%20President%20Trump%20has%20already%20said%20publicly%20that%20President%20Zelensky%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20have%20the%20cards%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20could%2C%20of%20course%2C%20discuss%20with%20the%20United%20States%2C%20even%20with%20European%20countries%2C%20and%20of%20course%20with%20our%20partners%20and%20friends%2C%20under%20the%20auspices%20of%20the%20UN%2C%20the%20possibility%20of%20establishing%20a%20transitional%20administration%20in%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20President%20Putin%20said%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20an%20Arctic%20forum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20for%3F%20To%20organise%20a%20democratic%20presidential%20election%20that%20would%20result%20in%20the%20coming%20to%20power%20of%20a%20competent%20government%20that%20would%20have%20the%20confidence%20of%20the%20people%2C%20and%20then%20begin%20negotiations%20with%20these%20authorities%20on%20a%20peace%20agreement%20and%20sign%20legitimate%20documents%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20indirectly%20calling%20Zelensky%20a%20dictator%20-%20something%20that%20President%20Trump%20has%20already%20done%20in%20the%20recent%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Putin%20also%20ordered%20his%20troops%20to%20press%20their%20advantage%20on%20the%20battlefield%20and%20step%20up%20their%20attacks.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20saying%20not%20so%20long%20ago%3A%20'We%20will%20finish%20them%20off.'%20Now%20there%20are%20reasons%20to%20believe%20that%20we%20will%20indeed%20finish%20them%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20President%20Putin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20gradually%2C%20not%20as%20fast%20as%20some%20would%20like%2C%20but%20nevertheless%20persistently%20and%20confidently%20moving%20toward%20achieving%20all%20the%20goals%20stated%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20special%20operation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUKRAINE%20BRACES%20FOR%20IMPACT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Andriy%20Yermak%2C%20Ukrainian%20presidency's%20chief%20of%20staff%2C%20has%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BRussia%20is%20trying%20to%20derail%20the%20path%20to%20peace%20by%20choosing%20to%20continue%20the%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20President%20Zelensky%20rushed%20to%20Paris%20to%20meet%20Ukraine's%20key%20European%20backers%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20strike%20a%20unified%20position%20of%20support%20against%20President%20Putin's%20aggression%20as%20well%20as%20President%20Trump's%20overhaul%20of%20US'%20policy%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20he%20claims%20is%20leaning%20towards%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20by%20the%20end%20of%20that%20meeting%20in%20Paris%2C%20President%20Zelensky%20said%20he%20was%20left%20with%20%26quot%3Bmany%20more%20questions%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bvery%20few%20answers%26quot%3B.%20The%20talks%20were%20led%20by%20France%20and%20Britain%20on%20a%20possible%20European%20troop%20deployment%20as%20part%20of%20any%20wider%20ceasefire%20or%20peace%20deal.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743159240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F8er9nevk_putin-zelensky-reuters_625x300_28_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fvladimir-putin-calls-for-zelenskys-removal-as-ukraine-negotiations-face-uncertainty-8031993%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20upped%20the%20ante%20in%20the%20negotiations%20to%20end%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20Going%20straight%20for%20the%20head%2C%20he%20has%20called%20for%20Zelensky's%20removal%20as%20Ukraine's%20President%20and%20instead%2C%20put%20in%20place%20a%20%26quot%3Btransitional%20administration%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fvladimir-putin-calls-for-z