%20astronauts%20Butch%20Wilmore%20and%20Sunita%20Williams%20stuck%20in%20space%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAstronauts%20Butch%20Wilmore%20and%20Sunita%20Williams%20embarked%20on%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F360476%2Fnasa-space-camp-for-students-astronauts-geet-alabama-us-space-rocket-centre-how-to-get-apply%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeight-day%20mission%3C%2Fa%3E%20aboard%20the%20Boeing%20Starliner%20(CST-100)%2C%20a%20spacecraft%20designed%20for%20crew%20transport.%20However%2C%20their%20return%20was%20delayed%20due%20to%20a%20helium%20leak%20in%20the%20propulsion%20system%2C%20making%20re-entry%20unsafe.%20%E2%80%9CEntering%20and%20leaving%20Earth%20is%20very%20risky%2C%20and%20this%20spacecraft%20faced%20a%20helium%20leakage%2C%20so%20it%20could%20not%20leave%20the%20ISS%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Rachna.%20Eventually%2C%20they%20returned%20via%20SpaceX%E2%80%99s%20Crew%20Dragon%20capsule%2C%20after%20spending%20nine%20unexpected%20months%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20did%20they%20sustain%20themselves%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20extended%20stay%2C%20Wilmore%20and%20Williams%20had%20enough%20supplies%20to%20survive%20comfortably.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20ISS%20is%20equipped%20to%20sustain%20up%20to%20six%20astronauts%2C%20so%20they%20had%20enough%20food%20stored%20according%20to%20microgravity%20conditions%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rachna.%20%E2%80%9CTheir%20diet%20consists%20of%20specially%20packaged%20foods%20and%20nutrient-rich%20fluids%20to%20counteract%20the%20effects%20of%20space%20travel.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMicrogravity%20takes%20a%20toll%20on%20the%20human%20body.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20heart%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20push%20blood%20as%20hard%2C%20so%20it%20becomes%20slightly%20spherical%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Rachna.%20%E2%80%9CBone%20density%20reduces%2C%20and%20muscles%20weaken%2C%20which%20is%20why%20astronauts